cardData.data: The value for call volume range from a minimum of 4 all the way upto a maximum of 78. The sum of call volume amounts to 80,850 with the average call volume per observation being 38. The dataset contains 2085 observations and there are no outliers.

The histogram shows distribution of call volume divided into 25 categories.

The plot indicates that the call volume observations are spread across many categories, as more than three quarters (77.0%) of call volume values are between 9 and 60. The distribution is positively skewed, which implies that there is a significant chunk of low-value call volume observations.
Concentration of High & Low segments
The top 34% of the observations (High segment) account for about 57% of the total call volume (80,850), i.e. 46,548.

• The overall call volume from the bottom quartile (28% of observations low call volume) amounts to 7,904, which is just 9% of the total.
  • The average call volume per observations for the top performing segment is 64, which is 1.65 times that of the overall average call volume per observation (38) and 3.9 times that of the mean value from Low segment.
How Call Volume is Changing over Time
This section provides insights on how Call Volume is performing over time and captures the most significant moments that defined the overall pattern or trend over the observation period.

The dataset contains Call Volume figures for a 12 months period. The values of Call Volume have dropped by 11.8% during the same time, from 7,088 in Jan-16 to 6,249 in Dec-16. The total Call Volume were 80,850 for the last 12 months, with the average Call Volume per month being 6,737.
Despite negative growth , there is no trend in the data. However, the Call Volume figures are unlikely to follow a seasonal pattern during this period.
The total contribution from the streak of 2 months (Sep-16 to Oct-16) amounts to a total of 15770.0, which is almost one fourth of the overall Call Volume for the 12 months period.

11.8%
Overall decline in Call Volume over the last 12 months

34.7%
Largest growth in Call Volume happened in Dec-16
Highest and Lowest Points of Call Volume

The Call Volume figures hit a peak of 8,105 in Oct-16, which resulted after a continuous streak of growth for 4 months ending at Oct-16. The most significant factor that fuelled this strong run is the Top Organization, Microsoft. Call Volume contribution from Microsoft in Oct-16, increased by over 141 percentage points (87.09 vis-a-vis 36.01) compared to rest of the observation period.

However, there are also few months when Call Volume was lagging and didn't do very well. The most notable among them was Nov-16 and values for Call Volume dropped to 4,638. This was primarily due to sharp decline in Call Volume from Docs for reimbursement Call Type, which observed a decline of over 11 percentage points (52.07 vis-a-vis 57.65).
Significant factors that drive increase in Call Volume

• Top Organization and Call Type have been very instrumental in driving Call Volume growth, as their respective levels Apple and Plan Limit witnessed the highest overall growth rates of 250% and 57% respectively.
Significant factors that drag Call Volume down
• Agent Age and Region have been an area of concern, as their respective levels 36 to 45 and Central shrunk by 32% and 6% respectively.

Docs for reimbursement's Call Volume Performance over time

Call Volume contribution from Docs for reimbursement is predominantly in line with the overall Call Volume trend, as the Call Type observed similar ups and downs during the observation period. The overall Call Volume figures hit a peak of 8,105 in Oct-16, when it grew by over 9.51% compared to the previous time period. But, Docs for reimbursement’s Call Volume peaked at 4,930 during Sep-16.

Impact of First call resolution on Call Volume
Overview

First call resolution is one of the significant influencer of Call Volume and it explains a great magnitude of change in Call Volume. It is positively & strongly correlated with the Call Volume figures. As First call resolution changes, Call Volume also tend to move in the same direction. An incremental unit change in First call resolution corresponds to an average decrease in Call Volume by -1.54 units.
Sensitivity Analysis

First call resolution seems to have a remarkable impact on various segments of Call Volume observations. The chart above shows four quadrants based on the distribution of Call Volume (high vs. low) and First call resolution (high vs. low).
